radiographic_examinations.findings: Clear lung bases; 12 mm lesion in segment V of the liver consistent with focal nodular hyperplasia or other benign entity; sludge and gallstones in gallbladder with mild gallbladder wall edema; no intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation; normal hepatic arterial anatomy; patent hepatic and portal veins; normal spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys; homogeneous pancreas; no retroperitoneal masses; normal bone marrow signal.
